<HEADLINE>
MANDARIN AIRLINES TO OPEN KAOHSIUNG-HO CHI MINH CITY FLIGHT
SERVICE
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kaohsiung,  April  26 (CNA) 04/26/07  21:55:34 (By T.C. Jiang)
</P>
<P>
Mandarin Airlines, a local airline carrier, will open regular
direct flights between the southern port city of Kaohsiung and Ho
Chi Minh City in southern Vietnam, starting April 29, a spokesman
for the company said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The new service will benefit those Taiwanese businessmen who
often need to travel to the Southeast Asian country, Vietnamese
spouses of local citizens, and travelers in southern Taiwan, the
spokesman noted.
</P>
<P>
The flight will take around 3.5 hours, the spokesman said, adding
that the tickets for the first flight have been sold out.
</P>
<P>
The airline company will offer a discounted ticket price for
flights between April 29 and May 12 to celebrate the opening of
the new route, the spokesman pointed out.
</P>
